<p>Say you have this generic <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/a/6884667/1576401">method</a>:</p>  <pre><code>    public static T ConvertValue&lt;T, U&gt;(U value) where U : IConvertible     {         return (T)Convert.ChangeType(value, typeof(T));     } </code></pre>  <p>If I want to call this method inside another generic method. The outer generic method must receive as arguments the actual argument values to set <code>&lt;T, U&gt;(U value)</code> of the inner generic method.</p>  <p>How to achieve this properly, so that I can call <code>OuterGeneric</code> and feed it with the appropriate arguments?  </p>  <p>This is just a demonstration of how I need to use it.  </p>  <pre><code>public void OuterGeneric&lt;TypeT, TypeU&gt;(TypeT tType, TypeU uType, TypeU valueOfTypeU) {    // Call of Generic method    TypeT recieverOf_T  = ConvertValue&lt;tType, uType&gt;(valueOfTypeU); }  // Some way to call OuterGeneric. How? </code></pre>